member.remarks:
                The event handler function is called with 2 parameters: 


A reference to the control object that
                    triggered the event;


                        An event arguments object with parameters specific to the control. 


Reason - an enumeration value containing the reason for the error: parse error, out of range, etc;

InputText - the currently entered text.

member.example:
    This example demonstrates the usage of the OnClientDown property. 

<script>
function onError(input, args)
{
   alert("Invalid character:" + args.NewValue);
}
</script>

<rad:RadMaskedTextBox
      ID="RadMaskedTextBox1"
      runat="server"
      Mask="<0..255>.<0..255>.<0..255>.<0..255>"
      OnClientError="onError">
</rad:RadMaskedTextBox>

member.remarks:
                The event handler function is called with 2 parameters: 


A reference to the RadMaskedTextBox object that
                    triggered the event;


                        An event arguments object that contains the following properties: 


OldValue - The old value of the text box;

NewValue - The new value of the text box.

